At least 25 people were killed and 38 injured when  a speeding passenger train came off the rails Monday in eastern Burma,  state-run Radio Rangoon reported.
The accident occured near Kayar village, about 400 kilometers (250 miles)  east of Rangoon, according to the broadcast monitored here.
The report said the train, which was carring both passengers and a load of  rice, "collapsed" after the wheels of the train left the tracks.
The engine and two passenger cars were completely destroyed, the report  said, adding that several others had been split, crushed or left upside down.  Meters (yards) of railway track had been torn up as well, it said.
Senior Burmese government officials, including Rail Transport Minister Win  Sein, visited the scene, the report said.
Rescue efforts were still underway it said.
